✅ Step-by-Step Guide
🔹 1. Extract the compressed file
Use your OS or a tool like WinRAR, 7-Zip, or tar to extract the project folder.

On Windows: Right-click > Extract Here or Extract to /folder/

On Linux/macOS terminal:


unzip yourfile.zip     # for .zip
tar -xvzf yourfile.tar.gz  # for .tar.gz
🔹 2. Open the project folder
It should contain something like:


/client       → React frontend
/server       → Node/Express backend
/package.json → Optional root package.json


🔹 3. Install dependencies
Open your terminal in the extracted root folder.

📁 For frontend (client):

cd client
npm install
📁 For backend (server):

cd ../server
npm install
📝 If both client and server are managed from root with a root package.json, you can just run:

npm install



🔹 4. Run the project
✅ Run Backend (Express):

cd server
npm start      # or: nodemon server.js
✅ Run Frontend (React):

cd client
npm start      # This will start frontend at http://localhost:5173/
